Ian Rosenblatt - Wikipedia





















 






Ian Rosenblatt

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Ian Isaac Rosenblatt OBE (born 2 November 1959) is a British lawyer,[1] senior partner of corporate law firm Rosenblatt Solicitors, and a supporter of charitable causes, notably in the field of classical music. He is the founder and sponsor of the Rosenblatt Recitals, London's only world-class series of opera recitals, inaugurated in 2000 and based since the 2012/13 season at Wigmore Hall.[2] In 2013 he launched the Branscombe Festival in Devon, and he is also Honorary Co-Treasurer of the Royal Philharmonic Society and a trustee of the Susan Chilcott Scholarship Fund for young singers. In 2013 Rosenblatt saved North West London’s long-established Les Aldrich Music Shop from imminent closure by becoming its owner.[3] He also supports a number of other musical causes and a variety of charities in other social and medical fields.



