Children & Immigration

by Jeremy Rosenblatt, Ian LewisJeremy Rosenblatt




 


 Bringing together family law and immigration law, this work promotes such areas as: how families and children settle in the UK applications of parents and children for indefinite leave to enter, or remain, with a view to settlement in the UK how such applications affect or assist children special immigration voucher schemes for parents and children

See more details below








Paperback


Item is available through our marketplace sellers.

3 New & Used from
$15.25





Save to Wishlist



9781859411971














Overview
Product Details







Overview



 Bringing together family law and immigration law, this work promotes such areas as: how families and children settle in the UK applications of parents and children for indefinite leave to enter, or remain, with a view to settlement in the UK how such applications affect or assist children special immigration voucher schemes for parents and children children of polygamous marriages primary-purpose marriages and the affects on children children dependent upon adult immigration applications children of visitors, students, holiday-makers, employees, business investors and artists all of whom seek rights of entry into the UK independent children who seek asylum or are abandoned children relying upon the political asylum application of parents children adopted overseas brought into the UK legally or illegally applications where rules do not exist and therefore cannot apply Local Authority duties and long-term residence concessions impact of immigration status on courts' decisions to make a children Act order children and deportation children and citizenship and acquisition of citizenship by birth, adoption, descent, registration and naturalization.Appendices include the Asylum and Immigration Appeals Act 1993 Statement of Changes in Immigration Rules (HC395 and HC 3365) and Home Office Circular on Deportation (DP2/93, DP 3/96 and DP5/96). The book discusses immigration procedures, appeal tribunal procedures and judicial review procedures.



